SciKit-Learn Logistic Regression Vignette
==========================================

Description:
    Demonstrates binary classification using scikit-learn LogisticRegression.
    Loads real-world normalized World Population Prospects / World Bank data
    (normalized_wpp_wb.csv), prepares a feature matrix by dropping non-numeric
    and identifier columns, splits into train/test sets, fits a logistic
    regression model, and evaluates with score() and classification_report().

    Target variable: ImmigrantsEmigrants (binary — whether a country/year
    record is net immigrant or net emigrant).

    Key sklearn API used:
        - LogisticRegression.fit()
        - LogisticRegression.predict()
        - LogisticRegression.score()
        - sklearn.metrics.classification_report()

Data:
    ../data/normalized_wpp_wb.csv
